{
    "text": "Body snatchers",
    "created": "Sat, 27 Aug 2022 01:29:46 GMT",
    "type": "outline",
    "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/08/26/012946.html?title=bodySnatchers",
    "subs": [
        {
            "text": "Years ago, in graduate school in Iowa City, I sat down in an armchair near my one window and took a bit of a nap. The night before I'd seen the new remake of <i>Invasion of the Body Snatchers</i>, and a sequence of fast scenes lodged in my mind. The invaders, who looked just like everyone else, were finding each other in public places such as parks and shopping centers. They'd shake hands and quickly pass over a package containing one of the pods that allowed them to take over the bodily likeness of yet another human. These body snatchers were accumulating across the city, replacing good people with grim, conspiring replicas.",
            "created": "Sat, 27 Aug 2022 01:29:48 GMT",
            "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/08/26/012946.html?title=bodySnatchers#a012948"
        },
        {
            "text": "At the end of my nap, I stirred there in the chair and found myself wanting to type a few words about the movie, or maybe something that had grown out of a dream based on the movie. I wrote the first draft of this little poem:",
            "created": "Sat, 27 Aug 2022 01:33:01 GMT",
            "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/08/26/012946.html?title=bodySnatchers#a013301"
        },
        {
            "text": "<b>A Private Club</b><br><br>After I learned<br>the secret handshake<br>of the Partners in Misery,<br>I saw it everywhere.",
            "created": "Sat, 27 Aug 2022 01:34:09 GMT",
            "type": "markdown",
            "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/08/26/012946.html?title=bodySnatchers#a013409"
        },
        {
            "text": "I probably tinkered with the little poem for a day, then handed it in for my graduate poetry writing class, where my classmates thought it was too short--surely more could be done with this promising setup, they said. The professor seemed to think that the little poem did what it needed to do.",
            "created": "Sat, 27 Aug 2022 01:35:25 GMT",
            "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/08/26/012946.html?title=bodySnatchers#a013525"
        },
        {
            "text": "That was in 1978 or 1979. Since then, for me, the poem's point remains true. Once you learn what cruel or selfish or power-hungry things people are capable of, you spot these things happening around you on a regular basis.",
            "created": "Sat, 27 Aug 2022 01:46:29 GMT",
            "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/08/26/012946.html?title=bodySnatchers#a014629"
        },
        {
            "text": "Another way of thinking about <b>Thank You For Your Servitude</b> by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/MarkLeibovich\">@MarkLeibovich</a> is to say that the book teaches a reader how to spot the secret handshake of today's GOP. It teaches (figuratively speaking) that today's GOP national party leadership is made up nearly entirely of grim, joyless, conspiring body-snatchers.",
            "created": "Sat, 27 Aug 2022 01:52:06 GMT",
            "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/08/26/012946.html?title=bodySnatchers#a015206"
        }
    ]
}

